						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the temple of Śrī Veṅkatēśvara (also called Sātāni maṭha).</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1336, Pushya śu.</hi> may correspond to 1414 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record the gift of a pillar by one individual (name not known).</p>						

